President Obama has announced his intent to appoint three individuals to key Administration posts. Rear Admiral Gerd F. Glang will be appointed Commissioner of the Mississippi River Commission. Lynnae M. Ruttledge will be appointed Member of the Commission on Long-Term Care. And Dr. James J. Zogby will be appointed Member of the United States Commission on International Religious Freedom. President Obama expressed confidence that these individuals will serve the American people well in their new roles.